hadoop
======

Install and configure the Apache Hadoop package from tarball.


Filesystem layout
=================

/opt/hadoop        -- symlink to the versioned installation directory /opt/hadoop-2.x.x
/var/log/hadoop    -- log directory for Hadoop and HDFS
/run/hadoop        -- where Hadoop will hold PID files
/var/hdfs/namenode -- NameNode persistent namespace and transaction logs
/var/hdfs/datanode -- DataNode blocks


Jobs you need to do manually after running the playbook
=======================================================

# su hdfs
$ hdfs namenode -format
$ start-dfs.sh


Role variables
==============

hadoop_version
--------------

Version of Hadoop to download and install.


hadoop_dfs_replication
----------------------

Value for the dfs.replication property. Defaults to 1.


hadoop_ssh_private_key
hadoop_ssh_public_key
----------------------

Required. Generate a keypair locally and put the content into these
inventory variables. Example:

  ssh-keygen -t rsa -P "" -f hadoop
